This paper focuses on neural architecture search for object detection, which is a subfield of computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also involves designing a search space and using a gradient-based method, which are common techniques in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper mentions hardware optimization, which is relevant to robotics (cs.RO) and neural engineering (cs.NE).
